            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-447] zkServer.sh doesn&apos;t allow different config files to be specified on the command line</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-447</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Unless I&apos;m missing something, you can change the directory that the zoo.cfg file is in by setting ZOOCFGDIR but not the name of the file itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I find it convenient myself to specify the config file on the command line, but we should also let it be specified by environment variable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
